('g_LPnAEACAAJ', '100 Statements about a Game of Thrones', 'A Song of Ice and Fire', 'Lennex', '2013-03', 'In this book, we have hand-picked the most sophisticated, unanticipated, absorbing (if not at times crackpot!), original and musing book reviews of \"A Game of Thrones: A Song of Ice and Fire: Book One.\" Don\'t say we didn\'t warn you: these reviews are known to shock with their unconventionality or intimacy. Some may be startled by their biting sincerity; others may be spellbound by their unbridled flights of fantasy. Don\'t buy this book if: 1. You don\'t have nerves of steel. 2. You expect to get pregnant in the next five minutes. 3. You\'ve heard it all.', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=g_LPnAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', -1),
('G_tNDwAAQBAJ', 'The Secrets of Ninja School', '', 'Henry Holt and Company (BYR)', '2018-03-20', 'Ruby sets out to learn her own secret skill at Master Willow’s School for Ninjas in this charming picture book that celebrates confidence, creativity, and kindness. Includes a craft for making a felt stuffed dragon! Master Willow’s Ninja School is a place where junior ninja saplings must learn many important skills: how to make themselves invisible, fight skillfully, meditate patiently and—most importantly—how to be brave and unleash their own secret talent. But Ruby’s no good at traditional ninja skills and she seems too afraid to conquer her fears. Can a quiet, gentle sapling really graduate from ninja school? Yes! Especially when she taps into her own special talents. A Christy Ottaviano Book', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=G_tNDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 160082),
