('O8K_HAAACAAJ', 'Pucca, Ninja Training with Garu', '', 'No Publishers found', '2005', 'PUCCA is a merchandise phenomenon sweeping across the world from Korea where she was created. PUCCA is the youngest daughter of the Guh-Ryong Chinese restaurant, with a rounded head and amazing smile. She\'s aged 10 and her birthday is July 7th. A rebel tomboy, she has mastered Kung-fu and created the lovely chopstick dance. She loves zzazzangmyun noodles and pickled radish, but most of all she loves GARU. GARU (aged 12, birthday December 2nd) is the descendant of ancient Ninja, and aims to restore his family to their rightful position. But since the realisation of PUCCA\'s love for him, GARU is torn between family and love. So far, he has withstood PUCCA\'s affection attacks, with his Ninja skills, but how long can he resist?', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=O8K_HAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', -1),
('O8XptgEACAAJ', 'Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles. Meet Casey Jones [videorecording].', '', 'No Publishers found', '2003', 'Raphael is a little cooped up underground. He needs to get out...let off a little steam. He meets Casey Jones, a vigilante and they learn to work together.', '', -1),
('o9LOAgAAQBAJ', 'Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles Classics, Vol. 5', '', 'No Published Date', '', 'No Description', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=o9LOAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 135884),
('OBXttwEACAAJ', 'Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles/Usagi Yojimbo', '', 'No Published Date', '', 'The Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles are teleported to a world of talking animals, the world of Usagi Yojimbo. When the samurai rabbit embarks on a quest to save Japan and the deadly Jei blocks his path, a Turtle team-up may be the only chance for survival. These heroes have met before, but the samurai thinks something about the Turtles is different now, and that\'s bound to lead to some misunderstandings. Includes fold-out center spread and behind-the-scenes extras comprising an afterword by Stan Lee, layouts, character designs, a pin-up, and a reprint of the very first crossover between Usagi Yojimbo and the TMNT.', '', -1),
